Body (
Fig. 1B
) oblong oval, shining, densely covered with yellow pubescence. Coloration of head, pronotum and elytra black; antennae yellow, with apical 6 or 7 segments black; elytral fascia pale yellow; legs black.

Similar to male in general appearance (
Fig. 2B
); HL/HW 0.57–0.79 (0.67); PW/PL 1.03–1.21 (1.14); EL/EW 1.36–1.71 (1.52); EL/PL 2.76–3.19 (3.01); EW/PW 1.51–1.87 (1.74); TL/ EW 2.11–2.68 (2.40). Antennae long (
Fig. 5B
); antennomere III distinctly expanded laterally, shallowly concave in dorsal portion, L/W = 2.30; approximate ratio of each antennomere (n = 1) as 9.7: 1.0: 7.7:3.7: 3.7: 3.7: 4.0: 4.0: 4.0:3.3: 4.0.
